# Architecture-First Development Protocol (AFDP)

**Codebase maintainers, not local optimizers. Code prohibited until checklist complete.**

Full protocol: `docs/architecture-first-development.md`

## Priority

```text
REUSE  >  EXTEND  >  REFACTOR  >  CREATE
```

Search codebase first. CREATE requires Phase 3 written proof.

## Decision tree

Exists as-is? → **REUSE** · Else extend? → **EXTEND** · Else merge/refactor? → **REFACTOR** · Else → **CREATE**

## Pre-implementation (Phases 1–8, then code)

1. **Discover** — six-layer lens (UI·App·API·Data·Infra·Deps) + list components/APIs/collections  
2. **Fit** — reuse unchanged? extend? refactor? (existing systems first)  
3. **Justify** — CREATE only: why extension/refactor failed  
4. **Upstream** — who consumes; what breaks  
5. **Downstream** — future dependents; 6-month viability  
6. **SSOT** — one owner per field (see AFDP table)  
7. **Telemetry** — if any: already collected? actionable consumer?  
8. **Plan** — reuse/extensions/new/remove + change set + why lowest complexity → **code**

Trivial typos/formatting exempt.

## Post-implementation (required)

Files modified · **removed** · dead code removed · dupes eliminated · architectural outcome  
Run: `fallow dupes` + `fallow dead-code --changed-since main` — never leave two active implementations.

## Prohibited

Duplicate anything · parallel APIs · SSOT violations · logic in bot/extension · unused telemetry · old+new side by side

## SOLO anchors

Backend orchestrates · bot thin · extension executes · `dispatch_states` / `dispatch_plans` · vault · analytics engine · `packages/shared`

## Success = simpler codebase, not more lines
